'''Mushroom Loft''' is a cross-platform [[Special:MyLanguage/Worlds|world]] created by Kireya. It was published in 2024. The entire world is part of the inside of a thick tree, inside a dense forest that has many large mushrooms around.

[[File:Mushroom Loft 1.jpg|thumb|Overgrown stained glass found at spawn. Photo by StephenVR]]

==Design==

The interior of the tree houses everything part of this world. Four different pods sprawl out from the center of the tree stem. Each one is designed to look comfortable. 

===Areas===

One of these pods is placed several meters above and is only accessible by using a ladder. It has a large bookshelf, a bed and a plushie that can be grabbed.

In the kitchen area, players can observe a knife cooking by itself, creating a whimsical and magical atmosphere.

A soothing relaxation area is surrounded by water, where players can:
* Teleport above the mushrooms using a button.
* Toggle flowers in the water or enable the "meditation" mode to create a peaceful atmosphere.
* Use a camera system that captures the surrounding area and displays it on a screen near the spawn point.

[[File:Mushroom Loft Lake.jpg|thumb|Pod with a lake found in Mushroom Loft. Photo by StephenVR]]

Players can access a hidden down area through a trap door located next to the spawn area.

[[File:MushroomLoftLakeTrapDoor.webp|thumb|The trapdoor that gives access to the down area.]]

==Lighting==

The entire world is lit by glowing mushrooms and several smaller balls of light. Candles round off the overall natural feel and are prominently found in one of the pods, which has a lake inside it.

==World interactions==

Players can interact with various objects within the world, including:

* A mushroom drink that causes a trippy effect for a short duration when consumed.
* Wands that allow players to create particle effects.
* A video player located in one of the ground-level pods.
* A Polaroid camera located in the higher-level pod.
* A message written on a paper sheet inviting players to give it to someone they would like to add as a friend that says "Give this to someone you would like to add as a friend."